import React from 'react'; const MenstrualHygiene = () => { return (

Menstrual Hygiene Tips

{/* Basic Hygiene Section */}

Essential Period Care Tips

    {/* Choosing the Right Menstrual Product */}
  • Choose a menstrual product that suits your flow and comfort:
    • Pads: Easy to use, ideal for beginners
    • Tampons: Great for active people, change every 4-8 hours
    • Menstrual Cups: Eco-friendly, needs proper cleaning
    • Period Panties: Leak-proof, best for light flows
    • {/* Disposal Practices */}
  • Dispose of sanitary products properly:
    • Wrap used pads and tampons before discarding
    • Rinse menstrual cups before sterilizing
    • Rinse period panties before washing
    • {/* Additional Care Tips */}
  • Wear breathable cotton underwear to reduce irritation
  • Stay hydrated to reduce cramps and bloating
  • Track your cycle to prepare better
  • Exercise regularly to boost mood and relieve cramps
  • Eat a balanced diet rich in iron and Omega-3s
  • Relieve cramps naturally with heating pads, herbal teas, and massages
{/* Product Care Section */}

Menstrual Product Care

Disposable Products

  • Store in a clean, dry place
  • Check expiration dates
  • Never flush pads or tampons
  • Wrap used products properly before disposal

Reusable Products

  • Clean menstrual cups by boiling between cycles
  • Wash reusable pads with hot water
  • Dry items completely before storage
  • Replace products according to manufacturer guidelines
{/* Common Mistakes Section */}

Common Mistakes to Avoid

Don't:

  • Use scented products
  • Wear wet swimwear for long periods
  • Skip changing products overnight
  • Use harsh soaps in intimate areas
  • Ignore unusual symptoms or discomfort
); }; export default MenstrualHygiene;
